We got home and avoided a ton of hassel so my wife and I are very thankful for the service. Would absolutely recommend this business to anyone.

review_text: We were very happy with this company. review_text: *****STAY AWAY From this Service******I used this service for nearly 3 years, services was mediocore but finally what really drove for me to sign-up to yelp just to post this is the complete lack of repeat customer appreciation and ridculous system. For the last six months I used them twice a week for aiport service, never an issue. This past thursday I had two reports of alleged no-shows with claim on the last no show that I the ( customer gave them wrong fligh number). Although they sent me an email with flight number they looked up and received both ridiculous challenge that I gave the wrong number. Indicating they dont give numbers but then stating they realized the filght was incorrect and sent me a voicemail. So first they don't do but then they do. It was completely absurd. My ordeal ended in me taking a yellow cab from the airport, being treated without any customer focus or service from Empire CLS. I am now moving to Jersey Limo and will find every post I can to share my experience to warn against a Empire CLS service that cares nothing for you loyalty and/or shows no understanding of customer service. FYI, Fare comparion you will find they also charge higher rates. So perhaps I should thank them!
owner_answer:
Hi, Oscar. Customer satisfaction is important to EmpireCLS, especially with loyal customers such as yourself, and we’re sorry to learn about your experience with us last year.

Our customer service specialists take additional steps to verify flight numbers given for airport pickups for accuracy and reach out to customers immediately if any discrepancies show up on our end. This helps us stay ahead of any last-minute changes or delays, and ultimately ensures our chauffeurs arrive on time.

Understand this reply is late, but learning from these types mistakes or miscommunications will help us improve our service. If you have anything else to share about your experience or improvements we can make, I’d like to hear more.

Brian Holcomb | Manager, Special Projects
(201) 588-2273 | brian.holcomb@empirecls.com

name: EmpireCLS Worldwide Chauffeured Services
review_text: I don’t understand why they didn’t hire me if they only have a 4/5 star review. Im an elite driver and they treated me like a vagrant.

name: EmpireCLS Worldwide Chauffeured Services
review_text: My father worked for years in this company as a chauffeur. He used to be requested by many celebrities, David Seelinger's close friends, and David Seelinger himself used to thank my dad all the time for his great work/service. My father suddenly got a heart failure and was at the hospital for a long period of time. My father got many procedures done at the hospital, he was in the SICU for quite sometime and it was a very hard time for the whole family. Considering the fact that my father was the only income for a family of 6, it was a tough time for all of us. My brother and I called the company and told them about my father's situation and I would like to say that I am just very disappointed that David Seelinger didn't even bother to ask about my father, didn't even offer him anything for his hard work. If you ask any of the chauffeur's that work there, any of the workers, any of the celebrities that requested for my father or even David Seelinger's CLOSE FRIENDS that used to request for my father specifically to be their chauffeur; they will tell you how amazing he was, how much they enjoyed his company, and how much of a great man he is. David Seelinger had a show "undercover boss" where he made it seem like he cares about his workers, but after what happened to my father thats not what it seems like. He used to always thank my dad for his service and work after telling him to do a trip for him and his friends, but when my father got the heart failure and he was of no use to him or his friends anymore, David didn't even bother to ask or check how my father is doing. It is just very disappointing at how things turned out. My father did not choose to stop working for your company, in fact he was very upset because he loved what he was doing and enjoyed it all. I at least expected one last thank you, or for you to ask about him, or check whether the man that worked for you for many years and used to always say yes to every trip you give him -- even if he was tired -- if he was alright or not. Also, the day my father went to the hospital, he was working on a trip, he completed it even though he was in pain, then he called the company and asked to go home because he was not feeling well. A great company means nothing when the people within are cold hearted and don't actually care about their people/workers as they say they do. Don't get me wrong either most of the workers there asked about my father and were great people. I am just disappointed at David Seelinger because my father used to speak very highly of him and he used to be very excited whenever he emails him to do a trip for his close friends. What a shame.
